text.__SUMMARY__: Habenaria mossii is a species of plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is endemic to South Africa.  Its natural habitat is temperate grassland. It is threatened by habitat loss.
text.Sources: Pfab, M.F. & Victor, J. 2003.  Habenaria mossii.   2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.   Downloaded on 21 August 2007.
